UPDATE public.blog_posts SET
  blocks_es = '[{"id":"e4d0d420-0dfd-4470-9b3f-0c7dea1dffa1","type":"paragraph","html":"La escena se repite en muchas agencias: el lunes todo parece encajar en el calendario, el martes aparecen dos urgencias, el miércoles se encadenan reuniones de «solo 30 minutos» y el viernes acabas negociando una fecha que el lunes dabas por cerrada. No es falta de compromiso; es que <strong>la capacidad que ves en el calendario no es la capacidad que realmente construye entregables</strong>."},{"id":"26a9b986-88e9-4c35-924c-4bc7473dac51","type":"paragraph","html":"Aquí vamos a separar capas, sin humo: qué parte del tiempo es solo ocupación visible, qué parte sí mueve trabajo con nombre y apellidos, qué señales puedes observar antes de que el equipo se queme y qué decisiones prácticas puedes tomar esta misma semana para dejar de prometer con una foto engañosa."},{"id":"44a589b1-c4ea-4ac2-91e5-19ffcfa533f0","type":"callout","tone":"info","html":"Si quieres alinear fechas, presupuesto y personas en una misma conversación, empieza por la guía de planificación de proyectos con cronograma y recursos . Y si tu problema ya es la sobrecarga silenciosa, la guía de carga de trabajo sin burnout te da señales tempranas y lenguaje para actuar a tiempo."},{"id":"97b5aba3-9b2b-4f1f-b799-19cf057ce593","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"1. Mapa rápido (para no perderte)","anchorId":"mapa-capacidad-calendario-productiva"},{"id":"352089f9-088c-47d1-90e9-3330bd6e9e46","type":"paragraph","html":"Este artículo está pensado para escanear y aplicar. Si solo puedes leer una parte hoy, entra por la checklist del punto 5 y vuelve luego al resto."},{"id":"20f360ec-18e4-4772-93da-4b35f4dc495e","type":"table","headers":["Sección","Qué aclara","Resultado práctico"],"rows":[["2. Por qué el calendario miente","Diferencia entre hueco visible y bloque útil de ejecución.","Dejas de prometer fechas apoyándote en horas ficticias."],["3. Entregables frente a ocupación","Cómo distinguir actividad de avance real.","Instalas señales observables en la reunión de seguimiento."],["4. Capacidad neta el lunes","Cuatro decisiones simples para ordenar la semana.","Recuperas foco sin comprar herramientas ni reorganizar media empresa."],["5. Checklist y anti-patrones","Guion semanal para managers y errores que se repiten.","Conviertes una charla difusa en acuerdos concretos."]]},{"id":"050c3509-1ef7-48a4-a983-6c817b78609c","type":"toc"},{"id":"327acb93-437d-41e6-9749-ff781a468a4c","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"2. Por qué el calendario «verde» no es promesa de entrega","anchorId":"calendario-verde-engana"},{"id":"774cf8c2-37bd-4d6e-bbac-846e72276be7","type":"paragraph","html":"El calendario registra <strong>compromisos</strong>; el trabajo real exige <strong>continuidad</strong>. Un bloque de dos horas entre reuniones puede quedarse en veinte minutos útiles cuando sumas preparación, cambios de contexto, mensajes urgentes y decisiones pendientes de otra llamada. Ese coste rara vez aparece en la vista semanal, pero sí aparece en los retrasos."},{"id":"0a82c781-b906-40ab-ab9b-413c4c7ff66f","type":"paragraph","html":"La señal de alerta no es solo operativa: también es humana. Lo notas cuando alguien empieza a entregar tarde y con menos criterio, cuando el canal del proyecto se vuelve seco y cuando el equipo vive en modo reacción. Si planificas solo con huecos visibles, estás midiendo escaparate; no capacidad productiva."},{"id":"eb23d75d-3319-4b12-a987-8a9046c0a055","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"3. La pregunta incómoda: ¿qué entregable avanzó hoy?","anchorId":"entregables-contra-calendario"},{"id":"08f80e6b-96c9-40dd-ad11-209155169d9e","type":"paragraph","html":"Un día lleno de actividad puede cerrar en cero avance real. Por eso conviene cambiar la pregunta de seguimiento: no «¿estuvimos ocupados?», sino «¿qué entregable se movió de forma observable?». Si no puedes señalar un cambio concreto en un activo del proyecto, esa supuesta capacidad no existió para planificación."},{"id":"653ce774-6136-4db0-992a-540a4a35b810","type":"paragraph","html":"Este cambio de lenguaje evita una trampa clásica: confundir reuniones, mensajes y coordinación con progreso. Coordinar es necesario, pero no puede comerse toda la semana sin dejar rastro en lo que el cliente va a recibir."},{"id":"642cce3e-5106-4be3-afd5-ee698dfe522a","type":"table","headers":["Señal en el calendario","Lectura optimista","Lectura operativa real"],"rows":[["Seis reuniones de 30 minutos en un día","«Solo son tres horas»","Se fragmenta la jornada y el trabajo profundo se desplaza a última hora."],["Bloque de foco de 45 minutos","«Ya está protegido»","Sin reglas de interrupción, ese bloque es decorativo."],["Semana ligera de reuniones externas","«Tenemos aire»","El aire se lo comen retrabajos, revisiones no previstas y cambios de alcance."]]},{"id":"cbb9d6a7-bee5-486c-b8b3-5bc19cab4cc4","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"4. Capacidad neta: qué puedes cambiar el lunes sin comprar nada","anchorId":"lunes-capacidad-neta"},{"id":"67aff901-b4e7-44ea-aa06-0a61fd79b6c0","type":"paragraph","html":"Antes de abrir otro tablero, toma cuatro decisiones visibles en la herramienta que ya usa el equipo:"},{"id":"70e498e4-6975-4510-8b5c-dca4c098c8e3","type":"list","ordered":false,"items":["<strong>Buffer explícito</strong>: nadie debería planificarse al 100 % de su agenda. Si no hay colchón, estás planificando retrasos.","<strong>Regla de reuniones</strong>: fija ventanas para coordinación y protege bloques largos de ejecución en días clave.","<strong>Timeboxing de entregables</strong>: cada bloque de trabajo profundo debe tener entregable, no un «misc» genérico.","<strong>Métrica mínima semanal</strong>: cuántas horas fueron de construcción real y qué entregable se movió con ellas."]},{"id":"ca0badbb-1c3c-4be6-a58f-557d3305950b","type":"paragraph","html":"Cuando alguien diga «esto es demasiado proceso», devuelve una sola pregunta: ¿cuántas fechas movimos el último mes sin cambiar alcance? Esa cifra suele ordenar la conversación."},{"id":"d0872536-b7f7-43a5-8ab0-6f74ee375dae","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"5. Checklist semanal y anti-patrones que drenan capacidad","anchorId":"checklist-capacidad-productiva"},{"id":"dda9cce6-f652-487d-8b14-c05432190dae","type":"paragraph","html":"Usa esta checklist en 20 minutos cada lunes. Si dos o más puntos salen en rojo, no necesitas motivación extra: necesitas ajustar carga."},{"id":"a14f384f-54b5-4080-89f4-e5c4d768a2b4","type":"paragraph","html":"La idea no es controlar por controlar, sino detectar fricción antes de que se convierta en retrasos crónicos o desgaste del equipo."},{"id":"6ffb854b-3e17-4125-9fc4-27a7d0a5d6e3","type":"list","ordered":true,"items":["<strong>Revisión de bloques largos</strong>: ¿cada perfil crítico tiene al menos dos bloques de 90 minutos esta semana?","<strong>Entregables con dueño</strong>: ¿todo compromiso de la semana tiene responsable y definición de «hecho»?","<strong>Topes de reuniones</strong>: ¿hay días que superan el límite pactado de coordinación?","<strong>Colchón de imprevistos</strong>: ¿está reservado y visible o está «fiado» al esfuerzo extra?","<strong>Riesgos tempranos</strong>: ¿ya sabes qué fecha puede romperse si entra una urgencia adicional?"]},{"id":"aa0c1337-1303-40f0-92ce-691562c0ba16","type":"table","headers":["Anti-patrón","Qué lo delata","Cómo corregirlo"],"rows":[["Calendario al 100 %","Todo el mundo «ocupado» y ninguna capacidad de respuesta.","Introduce buffers por rol y baja carga comprometida antes de aceptar más trabajo."],["Bloques de foco simbólicos","Hay bloques en agenda, pero siempre se rompen por urgencias internas.","Define reglas de interrupción y un canal único para escalados reales."],["Seguimiento sin entregables","Muchos estados «en progreso», pocos artefactos terminados.","Pide evidencia semanal de avance por entregable, no por tarea suelta."],["Optimismo por defecto con clientes","Se prometen fechas sin validar capacidad neta.","Separa compromiso externo de capacidad interna y comunica rangos realistas."]]},{"id":"b8d754c7-545b-4212-b576-994606e23391","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"6. Lecturas para cerrar el círculo","anchorId":"leer-siguiente-capacidad"},{"id":"faa888b7-e4ca-4438-b957-1c04099a45e2","type":"paragraph","html":"Si quieres profundizar, entra por el punto que más te está costando sostener en tu operación diaria."},{"id":"868fe62a-eac2-4a5e-a542-51e902b6dba8","type":"list","ordered":false,"items":["<strong>Qué es el timeboxing</strong> — cómo acotar alcance dentro de una caja de tiempo sin quemar al equipo.","<strong>Ley de Parkinson</strong> — por qué el trabajo se expande cuando no pones límites claros.","<strong>KPIs para agencias</strong> — qué números sí predicen margen y salud operativa."]},{"id":"6bee1328-7f36-4184-9545-e968a21fec7b","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Preguntas frecuentes","anchorId":"faq-capacidad-calendario"},{"id":"9b9a5713-4d78-4e91-ae2c-ff651bbc1337","type":"faq","items":[{"q":"¿Qué diferencia real hay entre capacidad calendario y capacidad productiva?","a":"La capacidad calendario es el tiempo que parece libre en agenda. La capacidad productiva es el tiempo continuo que realmente permite avanzar entregables sin interrupciones críticas. Para planificar bien, manda la segunda."},{"q":"¿Qué señal temprana indica que estamos sobreprometiendo?","a":"Cuando el equipo acumula estados «en progreso» pero no cierra entregables semana tras semana. Suele venir acompañado de fechas que se mueven por «detalles» y de trabajo profundo desplazado a última hora."},{"q":"¿Cómo calculo una capacidad neta realista por persona?","a":"Parte de horas contratadas y resta reuniones recurrentes, administración, soporte, coordinación y un colchón de imprevistos. Lo que queda debe incluir bloques largos de ejecución; si solo quedan huecos cortos, la planificación está inflada."},{"q":"Mi cliente exige una fecha cerrada desde el inicio. ¿Cómo lo gestiono?","a":"Puedes comprometer fecha externa, pero valida primero capacidad interna. Si no hay margen, ofrece rango o plantea qué alcance sale del sprint. Prometer por presión comercial suele acabar en retrabajo, desgaste y pérdida de credibilidad."},{"q":"¿Una herramienta de planificación arregla esto por sí sola?","a":"No. La herramienta da visibilidad, pero el cambio real llega con reglas compartidas: límites de reuniones, definición de entregable, buffers y decisiones de prioridad cuando entra una urgencia."}]},{"id":"61ab1fa2-cd65-4d14-9cdd-9e1128234787","type":"paragraph","html":"Si quieres que ventas, operaciones y equipo técnico trabajen con la misma foto de capacidad útil, el planificador de recursos de Taimbox te ayuda a aterrizar estos acuerdos en la semana real."},{"id":"3b19e458-d782-4d1c-a4d2-433761912463","type":"cta","text":"Explorar el planificador","href":"/planificador-recursos","variant":"primary"},{"id":"1c29a7e2-e65c-4aa5-ba0f-5f2d9e243dd9","type":"relatedPost","slug":"planificacion-proyectos-cronograma-recursos"}]'::jsonb,
  blocks_en = '[{"id":"7740c589-99d0-441d-9376-3c2cbd6d7e41","type":"paragraph","html":"You have probably seen this in agency life: Monday looks tidy on the calendar, Tuesday brings two urgent requests, Wednesday gets swallowed by \"just 30-minute\" meetings, and by Friday you are renegotiating a date that looked safe three days earlier. This is not a commitment issue. It is a planning issue: <strong>calendar capacity is not the same as productive capacity</strong>."},{"id":"5a8d0ba6-f80b-4b06-9c39-308b4d771c16","type":"paragraph","html":"This guide breaks it down in practical terms: what part of your week is visible busyness, what part truly moves named deliverables, which early signals point to hidden overload, and which low-effort changes you can make this week to stop promising against a misleading picture."},{"id":"f479659a-c653-4e9a-a2ed-6d98b5bd5823","type":"callout","tone":"info","html":"If you want one shared language for dates, budget, and people, start with project planning with schedule and resources . If your issue is already silent overload, workload management without burnout gives you early warning signs and practical framing."},{"id":"5ef09ade-c7e4-48a9-8749-4ed6a2061fdc","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"1. Quick map (so you can scan fast)","anchorId":"mapa-capacidad-calendario-productiva"},{"id":"e9a931ab-4041-4be6-aabc-8a9fefd70da9","type":"paragraph","html":"This article is meant to be applied, not just read. If you only have ten minutes, jump straight to section 5 and run the checklist."},{"id":"c0908db4-0b6f-495f-a818-6bd3e9180e6c","type":"table","headers":["Section","What it clarifies","Practical outcome"],"rows":[["2. Why the calendar lies","The gap between visible free slots and usable focus blocks.","You stop committing based on fictional hours."],["3. Deliverables vs busyness","How to separate activity from genuine forward motion.","You bring observable signals into status reviews."],["4. Net capacity on Monday","Four lightweight decisions to reshape the week.","You recover focus without new tools or a big reorg."],["5. Weekly checklist and anti-patterns","A manager script plus common traps that drain teams.","You replace fuzzy updates with concrete agreements."]]},{"id":"1aca6557-d1e0-4db9-8d4a-591901221379","type":"toc"},{"id":"0ede6310-2640-408f-b494-e5d154871e49","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"2. Why a \"green\" calendar is not a delivery promise","anchorId":"calendario-verde-engana"},{"id":"1d7df0a4-79b4-4193-b9c8-1a2530c03cf5","type":"paragraph","html":"Calendars track <strong>commitments</strong>. Delivery work needs <strong>continuity</strong>. A two-hour slot between meetings can shrink to twenty useful minutes once you account for prep, context switching, urgent pings, and decision leftovers from prior calls. That hidden tax rarely appears in planning views, but it always appears in missed dates."},{"id":"a197c85d-aea1-41fd-8cd1-c5f643f88ff1","type":"paragraph","html":"The signal is not only operational, it is human. You see it when quality drops, replies turn terse, and the team stays in reaction mode. If your planning logic trusts empty slots alone, you are measuring availability theatre, not productive capacity."},{"id":"2c8b03a7-94c0-469c-9b12-e2212c847bcb","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"3. The uncomfortable question: what deliverable moved today?","anchorId":"entregables-contra-calendario"},{"id":"e3384c04-ff8e-45ea-8227-250a94164735","type":"paragraph","html":"A fully booked day can still end with zero tangible progress. Change the review question from \"Were we busy?\" to \"Which deliverable moved in a visible way?\" If you cannot point to a concrete change in an active deliverable, that capacity did not exist for planning purposes."},{"id":"fdcef2e9-7149-4fd4-9e65-1bbebe212afc","type":"paragraph","html":"This wording shift prevents a classic mistake: treating meetings, chats, and coordination as progress by default. Coordination matters, but it cannot consume the week while leaving no trace in what the client will actually receive."},{"id":"a72f3eb4-5e16-497e-a5fc-1ce45bdb55c7","type":"table","headers":["Calendar signal","Optimistic reading","Operational reading"],"rows":[["Six 30-minute meetings in one day","\"Only three hours\"","The day gets fragmented and deep work is pushed late."],["A 45-minute focus block","\"It is protected\"","Without interruption rules, that block is symbolic."],["A light week of external calls","\"We have breathing room\"","Rework, unplanned reviews, and scope tweaks fill the gap."]]},{"id":"b872a9d4-27ec-4660-97aa-7558d9617dd7","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"4. Net capacity: what you can change on Monday without buying anything","anchorId":"lunes-capacidad-neta"},{"id":"957c836e-acc1-47cb-9568-5c8838ed7ff1","type":"paragraph","html":"Before introducing another tool, make four visible decisions in the system your team already uses:"},{"id":"512e3e5d-6982-44c6-ba3b-abff531392c4","type":"list","ordered":false,"items":["<strong>Explicit buffer</strong>: nobody should be planned at 100% calendar load. No cushion means planned delays.","<strong>Meeting rule</strong>: define coordination windows and protect long execution blocks on key days.","<strong>Timeboxing for deliverables</strong>: deep-work blocks must be tied to a deliverable, not generic \"misc\".","<strong>One weekly metric</strong>: how many hours were true build time and which deliverable moved because of them."]},{"id":"70464cce-63cc-4d48-bd08-ecb6434cf0dd","type":"paragraph","html":"When someone says \"this is too much process\", ask one question: how many dates moved last month without scope changes? That usually resets the conversation."},{"id":"d062a976-cc77-45bb-ad07-70ee7a67b03b","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"5. Weekly checklist and anti-patterns that drain real capacity","anchorId":"checklist-capacidad-productiva"},{"id":"eb583b8a-51f7-4923-9585-dbe03d7eae4b","type":"paragraph","html":"Run this checklist every Monday in twenty minutes. If two or more items are red, you do not need a motivation speech; you need a workload adjustment."},{"id":"10afa0c6-897e-4cdb-a29c-a2423c212fc1","type":"paragraph","html":"The goal is not control for its own sake. It is to catch friction early, before it turns into chronic delays or team burnout."},{"id":"3075418a-b14e-44ba-acb4-cd2f19075466","type":"list","ordered":true,"items":["<strong>Long focus blocks</strong>: does each critical role have at least two 90-minute execution blocks this week?","<strong>Deliverables with ownership</strong>: does every commitment have one owner and a clear definition of done?","<strong>Meeting limits</strong>: are any days above your agreed coordination threshold?","<strong>Visible contingency buffer</strong>: is it explicitly reserved or silently outsourced to overtime?","<strong>Early risk signal</strong>: do you already know which date breaks first if one more urgent item lands?"]},{"id":"5fe6976b-4a37-4a1a-ae00-e82662c5c6e3","type":"table","headers":["Anti-pattern","How it shows up","How to fix it"],"rows":[["100% calendar booking","Everyone looks busy, nobody can absorb surprises.","Add role-based buffers and reduce committed load before taking more work."],["Symbolic focus blocks","Focus time exists in calendars but gets broken every day.","Set interruption rules and one escalation path for true urgencies."],["Status updates without deliverables","Plenty of \"in progress\", very little shipped.","Request weekly evidence by deliverable, not by scattered task count."],["Default optimism with clients","Dates are promised before net capacity is validated.","Separate external commitment from internal capacity and communicate realistic ranges."]]},{"id":"f5fb12bf-5368-41fa-81aa-b4de8bdb4ef1","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"6. Related reads to close the loop","anchorId":"leer-siguiente-capacidad"},{"id":"1e8ac16d-329a-45a8-97fe-05689f6cc238","type":"paragraph","html":"Go deeper based on the bottleneck that hurts most in your current operating model."},{"id":"9842c290-08f5-4e2c-8276-af8eb804e478","type":"list","ordered":false,"items":["<strong>What is timeboxing</strong> — how to constrain scope inside a fixed time box without burning people out.","<strong>Parkinson''s law</strong> — why work expands when you do not set clear limits.","<strong>Agency KPIs</strong> — the metrics that actually predict operational health and margin."]},{"id":"fe5cd053-aa05-4e29-be61-6b84b5665049","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Frequently asked questions","anchorId":"faq-capacidad-calendario"},{"id":"b9ce5141-f9f2-4baf-945e-16b32897a35e","type":"faq","items":[{"q":"What is the practical difference between calendar capacity and productive capacity?","a":"Calendar capacity is time that appears free in scheduling views. Productive capacity is uninterrupted execution time that can move deliverables forward. For reliable planning, productive capacity is the one that matters."},{"q":"What early signal tells me we are overpromising?","a":"When \"in progress\" items pile up while completed deliverables stay flat week after week. It usually comes with repeated date shifts and deep work pushed into late hours."},{"q":"How do I estimate realistic net capacity per person?","a":"Start from contracted hours and subtract recurring meetings, admin, support, coordination, and a contingency buffer. What remains must include long execution blocks; if only short slots are left, your plan is overloaded."},{"q":"My client asks for a hard date upfront. How should I handle it?","a":"You can commit externally, but validate internal capacity first. If margin is thin, offer a date range or agree which scope leaves the sprint. Selling certainty without capacity usually ends in rework and trust erosion."},{"q":"Can a planning tool solve this by itself?","a":"No. Tools improve visibility, but results come from shared operating rules: meeting limits, clear deliverables, explicit buffers, and priority decisions when urgency appears."}]},{"id":"27732b63-f72b-4c45-b464-ef57a88e5221","type":"paragraph","html":"If you want sales, operations, and delivery teams to work from the same picture of real capacity, Taimbox helps you turn these principles into weekly execution habits."},{"id":"403b500b-b02f-409f-b431-363c0255fde4","type":"cta","text":"Explore the planner","href":"/planificador-recursos","variant":"primary"},{"id":"570f076e-96d8-4b76-95ac-6bcfdbd04a8a","type":"relatedPost","slug":"planificacion-proyectos-cronograma-recursos"}]'::jsonb,
  json_ld_es = '{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":"Article","headline":"Capacidad calendario vs capacidad productiva: por qué un equipo ocupado no siempre entrega","description":"Guía práctica para agencias: señales observables, checklist semanal y anti-patrones para diferenciar ocupación de avance real y planificar fechas con más credibilidad.","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Taimbox"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Taimbox"},"datePublished":"2026-05-06","inLanguage":"es","mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://taimbox.com/blog/capacidad-calendario-vs-capacidad-productiva-equipo"}},{"@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"¿Qué diferencia real hay entre capacidad calendario y capacidad productiva?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"La capacidad calendario es el tiempo que parece libre en agenda. La capacidad productiva es el tiempo continuo que realmente permite avanzar entregables sin interrupciones críticas. Para planificar bien, manda la segunda."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"¿Qué señal temprana indica que estamos sobreprometiendo?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Cuando el equipo acumula estados «en progreso» pero no cierra entregables semana tras semana. Suele venir acompañado de fechas que se mueven por «detalles» y de trabajo profundo desplazado a última hora."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"¿Cómo calculo una capacidad neta realista por persona?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Parte de horas contratadas y resta reuniones recurrentes, administración, soporte, coordinación y un colchón de imprevistos. Lo que queda debe incluir bloques largos de ejecución; si solo quedan huecos cortos, la planificación está inflada."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Mi cliente exige una fecha cerrada desde el inicio. ¿Cómo lo gestiono?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Puedes comprometer fecha externa, pero valida primero capacidad interna. Si no hay margen, ofrece rango o plantea qué alcance sale del sprint. Prometer por presión comercial suele acabar en retrabajo, desgaste y pérdida de credibilidad."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"¿Una herramienta de planificación arregla esto por sí sola?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. La herramienta da visibilidad, pero el cambio real llega con reglas compartidas: límites de reuniones, definición de entregable, buffers y decisiones de prioridad cuando entra una urgencia."}}]},{"@type":"SoftwareApplication","name":"Taimbox","applicationCategory":"BusinessApplication","description":"Planificador de recursos para agencias: capacidad útil, entregables y rentabilidad en una sola vista operativa."}]}'::jsonb,
  json_ld_en = '{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":"Article","headline":"Calendar capacity vs productive capacity: why a busy team still misses deliverables","description":"Practical agency guide with observable signals, a weekly checklist, and anti-patterns to separate visible busyness from real output and set more credible delivery dates.","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Taimbox"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Taimbox"},"datePublished":"2026-05-06","inLanguage":"en","mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://taimbox.com/en/blog/calendar-capacity-vs-shippable-team-capacity"}},{"@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the practical difference between calendar capacity and productive capacity?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Calendar capacity is time that appears free in scheduling views. Productive capacity is uninterrupted execution time that can move deliverables forward. For reliable planning, productive capacity is the one that matters."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What early signal tells me we are overpromising?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"When \"in progress\" items pile up while completed deliverables stay flat week after week. It usually comes with repeated date shifts and deep work pushed into late hours."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I estimate realistic net capacity per person?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Start from contracted hours and subtract recurring meetings, admin, support, coordination, and a contingency buffer. What remains must include long execution blocks; if only short slots are left, your plan is overloaded."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"My client asks for a hard date upfront. How should I handle it?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"You can commit externally, but validate internal capacity first. If margin is thin, offer a date range or agree which scope leaves the sprint. Selling certainty without capacity usually ends in rework and trust erosion."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can a planning tool solve this by itself?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. Tools improve visibility, but results come from shared operating rules: meeting limits, clear deliverables, explicit buffers, and priority decisions when urgency appears."}}]},{"@type":"SoftwareApplication","name":"Taimbox","applicationCategory":"BusinessApplication","description":"Resource planning for agencies: useful capacity, deliverables, and profitability in one operational view."}]}'::jsonb
